article.description: Reserve Brittany Rountree scored 14 points to lead five players in double figures and North Carolina (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 19 AP) routed UNC Greensboro 91-35 Wednesday night.
article.headline: Brittany Rountree scores 14 points, North Carolina routs UNC Greensboro
article.linkText: Five players hit double digits as N. Carolina rolls
article.story:
CHAPEL HILL, N.C. -- Reserve Brittany Rountree scored 14 points to lead five players in double figures and North Carolina (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 19 AP) routed UNC Greensboro 91-35 Wednesday night.

Chay Shegog added 13 points, and Krista Gross and Danielle Butts had 12 each for the Tar Heels (3-0), who have won their first three games by an average of 52.7 points. Laura Broomfield chipped in with 11 points and 14 rebounds -- her third double-double of the season.

Jarae Savage scored 10 points as the Spartans fell to 0-2 under first-year coach Wendy Palmer. The 56-point loss was the largest margin of defeat in school history.

The Tar Heels shot 56.1 percent to 22.5 for the Spartans, outrebounded them 48-45 and forced 28 turnovers.

North Carolina led 17-4 and 30-6 en route to a 46-18 halftime advantage.
